notesStmt.note:
This collection of grammatical treatises was compiled by a student in the late fifteenth century. It contains works by Donatus, Diomedes, Phocas, Priscianus, Caper, Agraetius, Asper Maior, and Laurentius Valla. A later note on front flyleaf vi states that parts were copied from Jensonâ€™s 1476 edition of Diomedes (the Walters owns a copy, shelf mark 91.450). On fol. 18r, an unusual brass initial letter was affixed to the page (it was reattached in June, 2016).
Please note: cataloging is still in process for this manuscript.

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Latin.

supportDesc.foliation: The first and last four flyleaves are modern additions; front flyleaves 5 and 6 are earlier laid paper, although they do not appear to be as early as the rest of the manuscript

p.signatures: Written in Roman numerals horizontally on lower corner of versos, just under catchwords, on last pages of quires
p.catchwords: Written vertically near gutter on lower corner of versos on last pages of quires

decoDesc.decoNote: Not illuminated; only decoration is brass initial letter affixed to page on fol. 18r (reattached June 2016), and fol. 1r may have trace of similar initial, now lost; text in brown-black ink

binding.p: Modern leather binding by Walters conservation department; replaced eighteenth-century Italian half-Russia leather binding

history.provenance: Created by a student in Venice, Italy, late fifteenth century
